<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0911 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book is the first to present the entire range of variations of availablesewage treatment systems using plants in consecutive, individual reports;this enables the interested reader to draw comparisons for himself. Inthe introduction a ''classical'' sewage engineer is given the opportunityof comparing available process variants from this angle, pointing outthe differences and particularities of those variants individually, andassessing purification capacity, cost, and operational data in relationto conventional sewage treatment plants. Short texts summarize and appraisethe contents of the reports and compare them with one another.</TEXT></DOC>